body:
Probably a duplicate of https://github.com/pydata/pandas/issues/4486

That was a bug with plotting frames/series with non unique indices. If you can upgrade to .13 (latest official release) or later this should be fixed. Let me know if that works.

Also, `read_csv` can take a URL as the first argument so you don't need the `wget` line.

You are right, it is a duplicate!

But as I follow the [install instructions](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/install.html) to get 0.13 on Mac, I got 0.12, [because it is not in pip](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/20206835/install-pandas-v-0-13-dev-version-in-python-2-7), isn't it?
